  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the dataset also contains 4275 negative samples.",
    "Model evaluation and analysis Evaluation metricsWe briefly review several popular metrics for polyp segmentation task, i.e., intersection over union (IoU), precision-recall (PR), specificity, dice coefficient (Dice), Fmeasure (F β) [97], mean absolute error (MAE) [98], structural measure (S α) [99], and enhanced-alignment measure (E φ) [100].In this survey, we focus on pixel-level performance within a single image (or video frame), with performance calculated at the frame level.",
    "TP denotes true positives, indicating the number of pixels accurately identified as foreground (or objects of interest) in the segmentation result, corresponding to actual foreground pixels in the true annotation.",
    "FP signifies false positives, representing the number of pixels incorrectly identified as foreground in the segmentation result, despite being background pixels in the true annotation.",
    "FN refers to false negatives, denoting the number of pixels inaccurately labeled as background in the segmentation result, while these pixels are foreground in the true annotation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Model evaluation and analysis Evaluation metricsWe briefly review several popular metrics for polyp segmentation task, i.e., intersection over union (IoU), precision-recall (PR), specificity, dice coefficient (Dice), Fmeasure (F β) [97], mean absolute error (MAE) [98], structural measure (S α) [99], and enhanced-alignment measure (E φ) [100].In this survey, we focus on pixel-level performance within a single image (or video frame), with performance calculated at the frame level."
  ]
